\title{OCapN: Object Capability Network Protocol}
\taxon{reference}
\date{2023}
\meta{author}{Spritely Institute}
\meta{external}{https://ocapn.org}

\p{Spritely Institute. \em{OCapN: The Object Capability Network Protocol}. 2023. Specifies CapTP (Capability Transport Protocol) for distributed object-capability systems. Used in the BCI pipeline ([[bci-0004]], [[bci-stage-4]]) to secure decoded neural intent as an unforgeable, attenuable capability reference.}
